# AiDE Project Intelligence — Amazon Clone

## Project Patterns
- Django settings module is `amazon_project` (NOT `amazon`)
- Apps: accounts, products, cart, orders
- Cart is purely session-based via `cart/cart.py` Cart class
- UserProfile uses post_save signal on Django User
- All URLs use slug-based routing for products/categories
- Templates live in project-root `templates/` (not per-app)
- Static files in project-root `static/`
- Bootstrap 5 via CDN (no npm)
- crispy_forms with bootstrap5 pack for all forms

## File Naming Conventions
- App-level URL files: `<app>/urls.py` with `app_name = '<app>'`
- Context processors: `cart/context_processors.py`
- Cart logic: `cart/cart.py` (Cart class)

## Model Notes
- Product.price = full price, Product.discount_price = sale price (nullable)
- Category uses slug, Product uses slug (both unique)
- Order.status choices: pending, processing, shipped, delivered, cancelled
- OrderItem stores snapshot of price at time of order

## Common Pitfalls
- Always include `{% load crispy_forms_tags %}` before using `|crispy`
- MEDIA_URL must be served in dev via `urlpatterns += static(...)`
- Cart session key is `'cart'`
- Login required views use `@login_required` decorator